article.headline: No. 25 Arizona State beats Yale 69-51
article.story:
TEMPE, Ariz. --  Promise Amukamara scored 15, Quinn Dornstauder had 11 points with 11 rebounds and No. 25 Arizona State beat Yale 69-51 on Sunday.

The Sun Devils (11-1) used a 16-2 run to extend a 10-point second-half lead to 56-32 on Katie Hempen's 3-pointer with 8:51 to go.

Hempen was 3 of 5 from 3-point range and finished with 14 points. Sophie Brunner and Kelsey Moos added nine points each. Brunner also had nine rebounds and Moos grabbed eight.

Yale (4-7) led 12-11 in the first half, but Arizona State took a 15-point lead with an 18-2 run. The Bulldogs finished the first half with only 22 points and never threatened ASU in the second half.

Lena Munzer scored 10 points and Emmy Allen grabbed 11 rebounds to lead Yale. Tamara Simpson and Sarah Halejian each added eight points.
